This paper is primarily focused on image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of regularization techniques for selecting informative parts, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of negative parts, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks.
